SIMPLE: sprout
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sprout
<hw>Sprout</hw> <pr>(sprout)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sprouted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sprouting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>sprouten</ets>,
<ets>spruten</ets>; akin to OFries. <ets>spr⟦umac⟧ta</ets>, AS.
<ets>spre⟦oacute⟧tan</ets>, D. <ets>spruiten</ets>, G.
<ets>spriessen</ets>, Sw. <ets>spruta</ets> to squirt, to spout. Cf.
<er>Sprit</er>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos>, <er>Sprit</er> a spar,
<er>Spout</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, <er>Spurt</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To shoot, as the seed of a plant; to germinate; to push out new
shoots; hence, to grow like shoots of plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To shoot into ramifications.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprout</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sprout
<hw>Sprout</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cause to sprout;
<as>as, the rain will <ex>sprout</ex> the seed</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deprive of sprouts; <as>as, to <ex>sprout</ex>
potatoes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprout</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sprout
<hw>Sprout</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS. <ets>sprote</ets> a sprout,
sprig; akin to Icel. <ets>sproti</ets>, G. <ets>sprosse</ets>. See
<er>Sprout</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The shoot of a
plant; a shoot from the seed, from the stump, or from the root or tuber,
of a plant or tree; more rarely, a shoot from the stem of a plant, or
the end of a branch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Young coleworts; Brussels
sprouts.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Brussels sprouts</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Brussels</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spruce</ent>⟦br⟧
